03/09/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- On Tuesday (2 September), Prime Minister Costas Simitis announced a new social programme, worth 1.7 billion euros and aimed at supporting families, farmers and small businesses. He said the government's goal is to ensure fair distribution of budget revenues.
In other news, Foreign Minister George Papandreou met on Tuesday with US Congresswoman Loretta Sanchez. They discussed stability and economic development in the Balkans, as well as co-operation in the fight against terrorism. (ANA, MPA - 02/09/03)
